WEBVTT

00:02.503 --> 00:03.836
OHH, YEAH!

00:03.838 --> 00:06.505
♪ POWERPUFF GIRLS
FIGHTING CRIME ♪

00:06.507 --> 00:09.141
♪ TO SAVE THE WORLD
BEFORE BEDTIME ♪

00:09.143 --> 00:11.610
♪ HERE'S THE TIME TO SHINE
WHEN YOU'RE FIGHTING CRIME ♪

00:11.612 --> 00:13.345
♪ POWER IT UP ♪
♪ WHO'S GOT THE POWER? ♪

00:13.347 --> 00:14.813
♪ WE GOT THE POWER ♪

00:14.815 --> 00:17.016
♪ BREAKING THROUGH THE WALL,
GONNA DO IT ALL ♪

00:17.018 --> 00:19.218
♪ WE DON'T QUIT ♪
♪ WHO'S GOT THE POWER? ♪

00:19.220 --> 00:20.853
♪ WE GOT THE POWER ♪

00:20.855 --> 00:23.389
OH! YEAH!

00:29.330 --> 00:32.464
[ GROANING ]

00:35.302 --> 00:37.336
GEEZ, BLOSS,
IF YOU GOTTA TAKE A LEAK,

00:37.338 --> 00:38.837
JUST TAKE THE PASS
AND GO!

00:38.839 --> 00:40.906
BUTTERCUP,
I DON'T HAVE TO GO!

00:40.908 --> 00:42.641
I'M JUST EXCITED!

00:42.643 --> 00:45.010
TODAY'S THE DAY
THAT DR. KENSINGTON Ph.D

00:45.012 --> 00:48.147
IS COMING TO TALK TO<i> US</i>
ABOUT THE SCIENCE FAIR!

00:48.149 --> 00:49.515
WHO'S ON
THE WHAT NOW?

00:49.517 --> 00:51.683
DR. RUPERT KENSINGTON,
Ph.D!

00:51.685 --> 00:53.685
HE'S ONLY
THE BIGGEST SCIENTIST

00:53.687 --> 00:55.821
IN THE ENTIRE
WESTERN HEMISPHERE!

00:55.823 --> 00:58.557
AND HE'S GOING
TO GUEST TEACH<i> OUR</i> CLASS!

00:58.559 --> 01:01.827
MAYBE HE CAN HELP US
PROVE THE EXISTENCE OF THE...

01:01.829 --> 01:03.429
GHOST HORSE!

01:03.431 --> 01:06.865
YOU MEAN THE ONE
THAT HAUNTS THIS VERY SCHOOL?

01:06.867 --> 01:08.167
THEY SAY AT NIGHT,

01:08.169 --> 01:10.369
YOU CAN HEAR HIM CLIP-CLOPPING
DOWN THE HALLWAYS.

01:10.371 --> 01:11.703
IT'S BOTH SCARY...

01:11.705 --> 01:12.871
[ NEIGHING ]

01:12.873 --> 01:14.706
AND ADORABLE!

01:14.708 --> 01:17.342
PLEASE!
THAT'S RIDICULOUS.

01:17.344 --> 01:19.244
OH!
HERE HE COMES!

01:19.246 --> 01:20.913
GOOD DAY, EVERYONE!

01:20.915 --> 01:24.216
AS SOME OF YOU
MAY ALREADY BE AWARE,

01:24.218 --> 01:28.120
MY NAME IS MISTE--
ERR -- DOCTOR...

01:28.122 --> 01:30.355
DR. RUPERT KENSINGTON,
Ph.D!

01:30.357 --> 01:32.958
WHY, YES!
THAT'S ME!

01:32.960 --> 01:39.531
UH, AND AS YOU MAY ALSO KNOW,
I'M VERY FAMOUS FOR SCIENCE-ING!

01:39.533 --> 01:43.068
WHY -- WHY,
I SINGLE-HANDEDLY CREATED THE...

01:43.070 --> 01:45.270
UH, THE, UH...
OH!

01:45.272 --> 01:46.905
THE TRANSMUTATION RAY!

01:46.907 --> 01:48.574
I'VE READ ALL OF YOUR BOOKS
ON IT!

01:48.576 --> 01:51.276
BORING. NO! DON'T YOU SEE?

01:51.278 --> 01:53.078
USING
HIS TRANSMUTATION RAY,

01:53.080 --> 01:55.747
HE INFUSED CARROT DNA
INTO A GRAPEFRUIT

01:55.749 --> 01:57.749
TO CREATE
A CARROTFRUIT!

01:57.751 --> 01:59.251
STILL BORING.

01:59.253 --> 02:03.422
A-AS YOU KNOW, I'LL BE TEACHING
YOUR CLASS THIS WEEK, AND --

02:03.424 --> 02:05.757
[ GASP ] "AND"?!
THERE'S AN "AND"!?

02:05.759 --> 02:09.495
I WILL BE JUDGING
YOUR SCIENCE FAIR NEXT WEEK

02:09.497 --> 02:10.996
AND --
AND?!

02:10.998 --> 02:15.100
AND AWARDING THIS, UH,
PRESTIGIOUS, ER, BLUE RIBBON

02:15.102 --> 02:19.138
TO THE STUDENT WITH THE MOST
IMPRESSIVE SCIENCE FAIR PROJECT.

02:19.140 --> 02:21.006
[ GASPS ]

02:21.008 --> 02:24.776
ER, ANYWAY,
I HOPE TO BE IMPRESSED.

02:24.778 --> 02:28.947
I HEAR SOME MINDS HERE
ARE RATHER SHARP!

02:28.949 --> 02:30.649
HE'S TALKING ABOUT ME!

02:30.651 --> 02:32.451
[ RINGS ]

02:32.453 --> 02:36.188
I KNOW WHAT PROJECT
WILL BLOW EVERYONE'S MINDS!

02:36.190 --> 02:38.257
"THE GHOST HORSE."

02:38.259 --> 02:40.626
[ WHINNIES ]
FACT OR...

02:40.628 --> 02:43.128
VERY<i> TRUE</i> FACT?!

02:43.130 --> 02:46.798
UH, BUBBLES?
I AGREE, BLOSSOM.

02:46.800 --> 02:50.469
THIS IS LITERALLY THE BEST IDEA
I'VE EVER HEARD!

02:50.471 --> 02:52.638
Both: [ Chanting ]
GHOST HORSE! GHOST HORSE!

02:52.640 --> 02:53.872
GHOST HORSE! GHOST HORSE!

02:53.874 --> 02:56.808
Rupert: BLOSSOM,
MAY I HAVE A WORD?

02:56.810 --> 02:58.944
AS MANY
AS YOU LIKE, SIR!

02:58.946 --> 03:02.314
AH, HAVE YOU GIVEN
ANY THOUGHT YET

03:02.316 --> 03:03.615
AS TO WHAT
YOU MIGHT DO

03:03.617 --> 03:05.317
FOR YOUR
SCIENCE FAIR PROJECT?

03:05.319 --> 03:06.718
OH, YES!

03:06.720 --> 03:08.987
I'VE BEEN COMPILING
A LIST OF MULTIPLE PROJECTS

03:08.989 --> 03:10.289
FOR MONTHS, SUCH AS...

03:10.291 --> 03:12.191
A BAKING SODA VOLCANO!

03:12.193 --> 03:14.826
A BIT SIMPLE,
DON'T YOU THINK?

03:14.828 --> 03:16.128
YOU'RE RIGHT.

03:16.130 --> 03:17.229
TORNADO TUBE?

03:17.231 --> 03:18.564
NO.

03:18.566 --> 03:20.499
ANT FARM DERBY?
NO.

03:20.501 --> 03:22.167
PAPIER-MâCHé BRAIN?
NO.

03:22.169 --> 03:23.235
COLD FUSION?!

03:23.237 --> 03:25.003
NO, THANKS,
I ALREADY ATE.

03:25.005 --> 03:28.307
I WAS THINKING OF SOMETHING
MORE ALONG THE LINES OF...

03:28.309 --> 03:29.641
THIS!

03:29.643 --> 03:32.311
A BLUEPRINT FOR
A GENUINE TRANSMUTATION RAY!

03:32.313 --> 03:33.545
YES!

03:33.547 --> 03:36.715
BUT PERHAPS IT'S TIME
FOR AN UPGRADE --

03:36.717 --> 03:40.552
SOMETHING THAT WILL MUTATE
NOT JUST PLANTS, BUT ANIMALS --

03:40.554 --> 03:43.155
OR EVEN HUMANS!

03:43.157 --> 03:47.359
YOU COULD MAKE, FOR EXAMPLE,
PEOPLE-SHEEP, OR SHEEP PEOPLE,

03:47.361 --> 03:49.394
OR UH,
WHAT DO YOU CALL 'EM?

03:49.396 --> 03:52.097
SHEEPLE?
THAT'S THE ONE!

03:52.099 --> 03:55.500
WHILE THAT DOES SOUND
LIKE AN AMAZING IDEA, SIR,

03:55.502 --> 03:57.369
WOULDN'T IT
BE DANGEROUS?

03:57.371 --> 03:59.938
AH!
TRUE, TRUE.

03:59.940 --> 04:03.442
BUT, SOMETIMES,
YOU HAVE TO DO DANGEROUS THINGS

04:03.444 --> 04:05.410
FOR THE GOOD
OF SOCIETY!

04:05.412 --> 04:07.679
THAT'S HOW HANG GLIDING
WAS INVENTED!

04:07.681 --> 04:09.915
NOT TO MENTION,
A PROJECT LIKE THAT

04:09.917 --> 04:13.885
WOULD CERTAINLY BE WORTHY
OF THE BLUE RIBBON AWARD.

04:13.887 --> 04:14.886
[ GASPS ]

04:14.888 --> 04:16.221
YES!

04:16.223 --> 04:20.892
AND THE PERSON WHO MADE IT
WOULD EVEN BE WORTHY OF BEING...

04:20.894 --> 04:22.861
MY ASSISTANT.

04:22.863 --> 04:23.895
[ GASPS ]

04:23.897 --> 04:28.433
OR, DARE I SAY,
MY LAB PARTNER.

04:28.435 --> 04:30.902
[ ANGELIC SQUEAL ]

04:30.904 --> 04:33.438
BUT MAYBE YOU'RE NOT
UP TO THE CHALLENGE.

04:33.440 --> 04:35.407
YES, I AM!

04:35.409 --> 04:37.309
EXCUSE ME,
DR. KENSINGTON,

04:37.311 --> 04:40.646
I HAVE SOME GROUNDBREAKING WORK
TO BREAK GROUND ON!

04:40.648 --> 04:44.416
[ MACHINERY WHIRRING ]

04:44.418 --> 04:47.819
[ BEEPING ]

04:47.821 --> 04:51.890
Ms. Keane: I'D LIKE TO WELCOME
EVERYONE TO THIS YEAR'S SCIENCE FAIR!

04:51.892 --> 04:54.059
LET'S GET ON
WITH THE JUDGING!

04:54.061 --> 04:56.895
HMM...NO.

04:56.897 --> 04:58.096
NO.

04:58.098 --> 05:00.165
MM, UNH-UNH.

05:00.167 --> 05:01.300
HMM.

05:01.302 --> 05:02.934
GHOST HORSE?

05:02.936 --> 05:04.603
YEAH!
THAT'S RIGHT!

05:04.605 --> 05:05.804
HIT THE LIGHTS!

05:05.806 --> 05:09.107
THE GHOST HORSE IS REAL,
PEOPLE!

05:09.109 --> 05:11.743
HAVEN'T YOU ALL NOTICED
HOW MESSY IT IS?

05:11.745 --> 05:15.314
THE JANITOR'S NOT BEEN DOING
HIS JOB BECAUSE HE'S BEEN...

05:15.316 --> 05:16.915
GHOST-NAPPED!

05:16.917 --> 05:17.949
[ GASPS ]

05:17.951 --> 05:21.086
AND WE'VE TRACKED
HIS GHOST PRINTS

05:21.088 --> 05:24.456
FROM THE BOILER ROOM
WHERE THE JANITOR HANGS OUT

05:24.458 --> 05:26.792
RIGHT
TO THE OFFICE OF...

05:26.794 --> 05:30.128
DR. RUPERT KENSINGTON,
Ph.D!

05:30.130 --> 05:31.296
[ GASPS ]

05:31.298 --> 05:33.465
WHERE ARE YOU HIDING
THE GHOST HORSE, HUH?

05:33.467 --> 05:35.434
I, UH...

05:35.436 --> 05:36.635
WELL, I...

05:36.637 --> 05:38.270
[ NERVOUS LAUGHTER ]

05:38.272 --> 05:39.638
OKAY...

05:39.640 --> 05:41.973
I THINK THAT'S ENOUGH
WITH THE CRAZY TALK.

05:41.975 --> 05:44.476
LET ME SHOW YOU
SOME<i> REAL</i> SCIENCE.

05:44.478 --> 05:47.045
THIS THING DIDN'T END
WITH ROSWELL,

05:47.047 --> 05:49.614
IT<i> STARTED</i>
WITH ROSWELL!

05:49.616 --> 05:52.484
I'M<i> SO</i> SORRY
ABOUT MY SISTERS, SIR!

05:52.486 --> 05:54.686
THAT'S
QUITE ALL RIGHT.

05:54.688 --> 05:57.322
NOW, LET'S SEE
YOUR PROJECT.

05:57.324 --> 05:59.624
I'M VERY EXCITED
ABOUT IT.

05:59.626 --> 06:01.693
[ SQUEALS ]
ME, TOO!

06:01.695 --> 06:03.729
I GIVE YOU...

06:03.731 --> 06:08.367
THE TRANSMUTATOR 2.5!

06:08.369 --> 06:09.668
HMM...

06:09.670 --> 06:11.002
ALLOW ME
TO DEMONSTRATE.

06:11.004 --> 06:12.070
[ WHIRRING ]

06:12.072 --> 06:13.739
AS YOU'LL SEE
IN THIS SIMULATION,

06:13.741 --> 06:15.374
I CAN USE
THE TRANSMUTATOR

06:15.376 --> 06:18.410
TO COMBINE THE DNA OF A HUMAN
WITH ANY ANIMAL.

06:18.412 --> 06:21.179
LIKE SO...

06:21.181 --> 06:25.217
WELL, THAT'S NICE,
BUT THAT'S JUST A DOLL.

06:25.219 --> 06:26.518
WOULD THIS MACHINE WORK

06:26.520 --> 06:30.689
ON REAL ANIMALS
AND REAL PEOPLE?

06:30.691 --> 06:32.224
YES, OF COURSE!

06:32.226 --> 06:33.658
[ Evilly ] GOOD!

06:33.660 --> 06:34.860
[ LAUGHS ]
WHA-WHAT?

06:34.862 --> 06:36.027
DR. KENSINGTON?!

06:36.029 --> 06:40.499
I AM NOT
DR. KENSINGTON.

06:40.501 --> 06:42.334
[ GASPING ]
IT'S THE JANITOR!

06:42.336 --> 06:45.570
I'D PREFER IF YOU CALLED ME
BY MY REAL NAME...

06:45.572 --> 06:47.305
[ GROWLS ]

06:49.343 --> 06:51.243
...JANITAUR!

06:51.245 --> 06:52.611
WHEW!

06:52.613 --> 06:55.046
THAT TAKES
SOME SERIOUS CORE STRENGTH.

06:55.048 --> 06:58.550
OH, AND HE'S A CENTAUR,
APPARENTLY.

06:58.552 --> 07:01.887
W-WHAT?
HOW IS THIS POSSIBLE?

07:01.889 --> 07:04.956
ALLOW US TO EXPLAIN.

07:06.860 --> 07:08.226
ACCORDING
TO OUR RESEARCH,

07:08.228 --> 07:10.262
THE GHOST HORSE STARTED
APPEARING

07:10.264 --> 07:12.864
AFTER THE SCIENCE FAIR EXPLOSION
OF 1992.

07:12.866 --> 07:16.234
DURING WHICH, THE STUDENT
WHO CAUSED THE EXPLOSION,

07:16.236 --> 07:20.572
WENDELL FEINSTEIN -- THE MOST
CARELESS STUDENT IN SCHOOL --

07:20.574 --> 07:22.240
DISAPPEARED!

07:22.242 --> 07:25.911
SOMETIME LATER,
A NEW JANITOR WAS HIRED...

07:25.913 --> 07:30.582
A JANITOR WITH A POSTERIOR
MOST SUPERIOR.

07:30.584 --> 07:33.084
WHAT?
HE HAD A GIANT BUTT!

07:33.086 --> 07:35.787
THAT DUDE'S
THE REAL GHOST HORSE!

07:35.789 --> 07:38.757
THANKS FOR
THE INTRODUCTION, GIRLS.

07:38.759 --> 07:40.425
NOW TO UNLEASH MY PLAN,

07:40.427 --> 07:44.262
AND MAKE ALL OF YOU HALF-ANIMAL
FREAKS -- LIKE ME!

07:44.264 --> 07:47.432
WHY DIDN'T YOU JUST HAVE ME BUILD A
MACHINE TO MAKE YOU HUMAN AGAIN?

07:47.434 --> 07:48.600
[ CRICKETS CHIRPING ]

07:48.602 --> 07:51.269
OH! WHY DIDN'T I
THINK OF THAT!

07:51.271 --> 07:52.637
MOST CARELESS STUDENT.

07:52.639 --> 07:55.607
[ GROWLS ]

07:55.609 --> 07:57.242
EEP!

08:00.147 --> 08:03.081
OH, MY GOSH!
THEY'RE SO CUTE!

08:03.083 --> 08:04.449
AHH!

08:04.451 --> 08:06.751
HUH?
I'M A BEE?

08:06.753 --> 08:09.521
YAY!
I'M A BEE!

08:09.523 --> 08:10.655
BUBBS, NO!

08:10.657 --> 08:11.790
AAH!

08:11.792 --> 08:13.625
[ SQUAWKS ]

08:13.627 --> 08:15.660
WOW. AWESOME...

08:15.662 --> 08:18.129
A FLAMINGO.

08:18.131 --> 08:19.664
[ GRUNTING ]

08:19.666 --> 08:21.666
HEY! WHOA!

08:21.668 --> 08:24.269
WATCH OUT!
OH, BOY!

08:24.271 --> 08:25.437
EXCUSE ME.

08:25.439 --> 08:29.708
OKAY, JANITAUR,
TIME TO BRING DOWN THE HAMMER!

08:29.710 --> 08:33.211
HYAH!

08:33.213 --> 08:34.312
HELP ME!

08:34.314 --> 08:35.981
I'M DR. KENSINGTON --

08:35.983 --> 08:38.016
THE<i> REAL</i> DR. KENSINGTON!

08:38.018 --> 08:41.620
WAIT!<i> YOU'RE</i>
THE REAL DR. KENSINGTON?

08:41.622 --> 08:43.188
OH, MY GOSH!

08:43.190 --> 08:44.723
I CAN'T BELIEVE
IT'S REALLY YOU!

08:44.725 --> 08:45.991
SIR, I JUST
WANT TO SAY --

08:45.993 --> 08:47.192
AAH!

08:47.194 --> 08:49.060
DR. KENSINGTON!

08:49.062 --> 08:52.664
I WILL AVENGE THEE
IN THE NAME OF SCIENCE!

08:52.666 --> 08:54.566
[ GRUNTS ]
OOF!

08:54.568 --> 08:56.368
[ LAUGHS ]

08:56.370 --> 09:00.171
AND NOW TO TURN ALL OF
TOWNSVILLE INTO FREAKS LIKE ME!

09:00.173 --> 09:01.306
ORT, ORT!

09:01.308 --> 09:05.343
BUBBLES, BUTTERCUP,
STOP HIM!

09:05.345 --> 09:07.579
♪ OH, YEAH ♪

09:07.581 --> 09:10.248
HELLO.
I'M HERE TO BUG YOU!

09:10.250 --> 09:11.650
[ GIGGLES ]

09:11.652 --> 09:13.718
UGH, GROSS!
STOP IT! GO AWAY!

09:13.720 --> 09:14.719
[ SQUAWKS ]

09:14.721 --> 09:16.521
QUIT IT!
KNOCK IT OFF!

09:16.523 --> 09:17.522
[ SQUAWKS ]

09:17.524 --> 09:19.391
GRRRRR!
STOP IT!

09:19.393 --> 09:21.693
[ GRUNTING ]

09:21.695 --> 09:22.694
[ MUNCH! ]

09:22.696 --> 09:25.330
[ PAINFUL SQUEAK ]

09:25.332 --> 09:27.666
[ SCREAMS ]

09:27.668 --> 09:30.535
[ WHOOSH! ]

09:30.537 --> 09:32.871
HUH?
[ GROWLS ]

09:32.873 --> 09:34.039
Both: WE DID IT!

09:34.041 --> 09:35.440
IT DOESN'T MATTER!

09:35.442 --> 09:38.410
THERE'S NO WAY
TO REVERSE THE EFFECTS NOW!

09:38.412 --> 09:39.544
[ LAUGHS ]

09:39.546 --> 09:40.545
[ SEAL BARKING ]

09:40.547 --> 09:41.780
Blossom: OR IS THERE?!

09:41.782 --> 09:45.584
YOU FORGOT,
I'M AN ORT-VER ACHIEVER!

09:48.422 --> 09:51.189
[ CHEERING ]

09:52.893 --> 09:54.526
WHOA, SWEET!

09:54.528 --> 09:55.627
[ GROANS ]

09:55.629 --> 09:58.296
YOU!<i> YOU!</i>
THAT'S RIGHT!

09:58.298 --> 10:00.231
I KNEW THE RAY
WAS TOO DANGEROUS,

10:00.233 --> 10:03.234
SO I BUILT A SECOND DEVICE
TO REVERSE THE EFFECTS.

10:03.236 --> 10:04.569
NO!

10:04.571 --> 10:07.806
WHEN YOU GET A CHANCE,
COULD YOU SWEEP THIS MESS UP?

10:07.808 --> 10:10.875
THANKS.
[ SIGHS ]

10:10.877 --> 10:13.111
AND SO THE WINNER

10:13.113 --> 10:16.648
OF THE SCIENCE FAIR AND BLUE
RIBBON AWARD GOES TO...

10:16.650 --> 10:18.717
AW.
I DON'T DESERVE TO WIN.

10:18.719 --> 10:21.720
...BUBBLES AND BUTTERCUP!

10:21.722 --> 10:22.988
[ CHEERING ]

10:22.990 --> 10:25.256
AW. I KIND OF THOUGHT
I WAS STILL GONNA WIN.

10:25.258 --> 10:27.392
BUBBLES AND BUTTERCUP'S
PROJECT

10:27.394 --> 10:29.995
WAS NOT ONLY PROVEN
THROUGH -- AHEM --

10:29.997 --> 10:32.097
A FORM
OF SCIENTIFIC METHOD,

10:32.099 --> 10:35.433
IT ALSO DIDN'T COMPROMISE
THEIR SCIENTIFIC INTEGRITY.

10:35.435 --> 10:38.970
I COULDN'T AGREE MORE,
DOCTOR KENSINGTON, Ph.D!

10:38.972 --> 10:40.338
<i> BUT...</i>

10:40.340 --> 10:43.074
IS THIS<i> REALLY</i>
THE END OF THE MYSTERY?

10:43.076 --> 10:46.978
OR IS THIS NOT THE REAL
DR. KENSINGTON, EITHER?

10:46.980 --> 10:48.947
ER, WHAT?!
[ SCREAMS ]

10:48.949 --> 10:50.281
GUYS, STOP!

10:50.283 --> 10:52.951
Buttercup:
REMOVE YOUR MASK, IMPOSTER!

10:52.953 --> 10:54.953
Rupert:
I'M NOT AN IMPOSTER!

10:54.955 --> 10:59.257
[ MUTTERING ]
STUPID SCIENCE!

10:59.259 --> 11:01.426
[ MUTTERING ]

11:03.463 --> 11:05.130
♪ POWERPUFF GIRLS
FIGHTING CRIME ♪

11:05.132 --> 11:07.699
♪ SAVING THE WORLD
BEFORE BEDTIME ♪

11:07.701 --> 11:10.535
♪ BATTLING EVIL TOE-TO-TOE ♪

11:10.537 --> 11:14.673
♪ SAVING THE DAY,
A POWERPUFF GOAL ♪
